## UX Patterns

### Navigation
- **Tab bar** for primary navigation (bottom, thumb-reachable)
- **Swipe gestures** for switching contexts (swipe between bots, swipe to delete)
- **Pull-to-refresh** for manual sync
- **Long-press** for contextual options (replaces right-click)
- **Back swipe** (edge gesture) for navigation stack

### Thumb Zone Design
```
┌──────────────────┐
│                  │  ← Stretch zone (status, title)
│                  │
│   NATURAL ZONE   │  ← Content (scrollable)
│                  │
│   PRIMARY ACTS   │  ← Thumb zone (main actions)
├──────────────────┤
│    TAB BAR       │  ← Navigation
└──────────────────┘
```

### Progressive Disclosure
- **Level 1:** Summary/preview (list view, cards)
- **Level 2:** Detail (tap to expand, full content)
- **Level 3:** Advanced (tap "More", settings, debug)

